{
  "text": "In satellite communications, the length of the round trip propagation delay makes power control error (PCE) inevitable. PCE is assumed to be log-normally distributed and the effect of it can be studied by multiplying the transmitted power by a log random variable [CITATION_1] . The transmitted power to user-k becomes:",
